sub_title: Finance PhD Student at Kelley School of Business
summary:
I am a finance lover nerd and an ex-entrepreneur with two different startups. 

I use my finance knowledge and quantitative skills to work on huge Excel tables of complicated financial statements, code to clean and manage the data in Python and solve entrepreneurial finance problems. 

My research interests lie in corporate finance, entrepreneurial finance, investment, and behavioral finance.

I enjoy sharing a drink with my friends, running, trying new sports and different cuisines, playing guitar, coding, teaching, writing, reading, and doing research :)

projects:
[{'title': 'ConFarm', 'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'description': 'We designed a farm for the future which uses hydroponic farming in our special transparent containers and can be used everywhere from developed cities to the distant villages of Africa! As long as there is enough energy, you can farm anywhere you want to by using our containers. The main materials for these containers are transparent polycarbonate, (allowing use of sunlight) and rock wool (for thermal insulation). In places where sunlight is insufficient for agriculture, efficiency can be increased by using the purple led lights of our containers. Moreover, our customers will not have to deal with learning about vertical agriculture details thanks to our mobile application that provides containers' conditions and crop ripeness, allowing them to know when to visit their containers. If our customers just want fresh products without dealing with farming, we also provide "city farmers" for them through the use of our agriculture network. As a result, we also create employment for people with farming skills, especially younger people, eager to learn about agriculture. Even if we are targeting well-off people living in cities desiring fresh products our buy-1-give-¼ business model also helps those in disadvantaged areas. With the help of this business model, we can reach not only people in big cities but also people in underdeveloped countries that need healthy food. 
 
We are the Hustler Elif is a business administration student responsible for the financial and administrative process, the Hipster Şeyma is a computer engineering student responsible for designing the application and improving UI/UX, the Hacker Erdem is an electrical and electronics engineering student responsible for developing the special containers and vertical-hydroponic farming systems. All members of the ConFarm believe in the power of agriculture as much as this team can change the world!
